column16: We are testing whether IMDb and Metacritic reviews are significantly
different from each other for the same movies from the top 150 list
Assumption: Because n > 30, we can assume equal variances
Null Hypothesis H0: The population means are the same
Alternative Hypothesis HA: The population means are not the same
Let us assume that Metacritic ratings are IMDb rating/10, so 9 IMDb = 90
Metacritic. Since IMDb mean > Metacritic mean, use a one-tailed t-test
Conclusion: Because our t-statistic value is larger than our one-tailed
t-critical value and our p-value is smaller than our alpha level of 0.05,
We can reject the null hypothesis and conclude that IMDb and Metacritic
rate the same movies differently. Specifically, IMDb rates higher on average
